					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The third part of the commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the book of Isaiah.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="272v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש ישעיהו </title>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Yesha῾yahu</title>
							<note>
								<p>Contains the pointed Hebrew biblical text of Isaiah 44:6-46, accompanied by an Arabic translation and a commentary.</p>
								<p>Has a number of masoretic notes, some of them added by a later hand.</p>
								<p>The beginning and end of the hafṭarot are marked in the margins.</p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
							<filiation>Uniform with <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">280</ref>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex, semi-cursive script of approximately 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>272 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>205</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>158</height>
										<width>103</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>272 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>29 quires of 10 leaves each, with exception of the 1st and 10th which have 3 leaves each, and the 19th which have 9 leaves.</p>
									<p>Quires signed with Hebrew letters and Arabic words on theupper margin of the first page.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Several of the extant folios have been more or less damaged and/or mutilated.</p>
									<p>Lacuane after folios: 170, 227, 272.</p>
									<p>Water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="17" writtenLines="17">
									<p>Has masoretic notes in the margins.</p>
									<p>Hebrew biblical text is embodied.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
